Returns:

addUIShellRecentItem

public static TaskFlowObject addUIShellRecentItem(java.lang.String viewId,
                                                  java.lang.String webApp,
                                                  java.lang.String pageParameterslist,
                                                  java.lang.String taskFlowId,
                                                  java.lang.String keyList,
                                                  java.lang.String taskParametersList,
                                                  java.lang.String label,
                                                  FndMethodParameters methodParameters)
Adds the new UIShell recent items entry for an Object with the specified details. Taskflow navigations are implicitly added to UIShell Recent items. This api should be used to add recent items entry for specific Objects. The Object details like object id, object name, object type, context code should be set in the FndMethodParameters instance passed to this api.

Parameters:
viewId - viewId of the target page.
webApp - Deployed Module Name of the target workspace. If this is null, then the webApp name is set as the current webApp name.
pageParameterslist - Parameters list for the page. This is a semicolon delimited String of name value pairs. For example "param1=value1;param2=value2"
taskFlowId - ID of the taskFlow to open in the target page.
keyList - Key list to pass into the task flow to open in the target page. This is a semicolon delimited keys or key-value pairs. For example, "key1;key2=value2"
taskParametersList - Parameters list to pass in to the task flow to open in the target page. This is a semicolon delimited String of name value pairs. For example,"param1=value1;param2=value2."
label - Label for the task flow to open in the target workspace.
methodParameters - Construct FndMethodParameters object for passing additional information such as object id, object type, context code, object name, setting the width of contextual area, and/or setting the disclosed state of the contextual area.
Returns:
Returns a TaskFlowObject corresponding to the newly added recent item. Returns null if the recent items entry cannot be created.
